A clash erupted in Dera Bugti when armed men from the Bugti tribe attacked a convoy of soldiers.
Gunbattles continued throughout the day, with rebels using light and heavy weapons.
The tribesmen demanded autonomy and benefits from natural resources, leading to fierce clashes.
The violence escalated after a doctor's rape near the Sui gasfield.
The situation worsened as thousands fled due to threats from tribal chief Nawab Akbar Bugti.
The army deployed troops, and tensions rose as armed tribesmen surrounded government officials.
